<h2 id="section-top">Teenage and young adult cancer services</h2>
</div>
<div class="col four-sm">
</div>
<div class="col three-sm" id="ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_PlaceHolderMain_contentColumn1">
<div class="box">
<p class="module">
        This Department is managed by  
        <a href="/Services/Trusts/Overview/DefaultView.aspx?id=1470">University Hospitals Birmingham NHS Foundation Trust</a>
</p>
<div class="panel">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<div class="service-locations clear">
<div class="panel edit-box">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<p class="address">Birmingham, B15 2TH <br/>0121 627 8426</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="panel">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<div id="imageContent47b055ed03bb4815a6d03908bc18bafc">
<div class="profile-pic">
<img alt="YPU" border="0" id="ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_PlaceHolderMain_column1Content_column1Content_SummaryAndPhotoModule_PhotoView_DisplayImage" src="/Services/UserControls/UploadHandlers/MediaServerHandler.ashx?id=248"/>
</div>
</div>
<p>The Young Persons Unit (YPU) is the inpatient hub of the Teenage and Young Adult (TYA) Service.  We treat a wide range of cancers from the very common to the very rare. Patients are mainly admitted for chemotherapy treatment and symptom control. The unit is an eight-bedded ward for young people from 16-25 years old. There are two three bedded bays and two side rooms, with a shared lounge, kitchen and study rooms. The Eden Room provides the perfect space to relax and unwind. We aim to provide a relaxed, 'home from home' environment with lots to do; free internet access enables patients to keep in touch with friends and family, arts and crafts materials, a TV and  DVD at every bedside, Sky TV, games consoles and jukebox in the lounge. The patient kitchen means that snacks and drinks can be brought in from home to eat whenever you like. There is even a sitting room for visitors to escape to. We have the staff and equipment to make a stay in hospital as comfortable as possible.</p>
<ul>
<li>Single sex bays</li>
<li>Open visiting times</li>
<li>One friend or family member (over 16) can stay overnight </li>
<li>Mobiles on!</li>
<li>Activities on and off the ward lead by the Youth Support Coordinator</li>
<li>Education and Employment support</li>
<li>Therapeutic massage</li>
<li>Guitar tutor</li>
<li>‘Look Good, Feel Better’ days</li>
<li>Health and Welfare advice</li>
</ul>
<p>If you want to have a peek at the unit, take a look at the short film ‘YPU Undressed’ made by patients on Jimmy Teens TV : http://www,jimmyteenstv.tv/2009/09/ypu-undressed/</p>
<p>In April 2011 it's all change as we move into our brand new state of the art hospital, the Queen Elizabeth Hospital Birmingham.  The unit will be bigger and better, enabling us to take 12 patients and the social rooms are improved to meet our needs. This has been supported by Teenage Cancer Trust and Queen Elizabeth Hospital Birmingham Charity.</p>
<p>For patients whose treatment requires admission to other specialist departments in the hospital, the TYA service (see team) will bring the essence, opportunities and equipment of the unit to them.</p></div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="panel name-thingsshouldknowmodule">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<h3>Things you should know</h3>
<p>You should bring your own day &amp; nightwear. You can personalise your bed space with bedding, posters &amp; photographs. Visitors are welcome &amp; we can accommodate 1 person overnight.  There are overnight facilities for additional visitors &amp; discounted parking. Snacks &amp; drinks can be prepared at any time.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="panel name-serviceteamsummary">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear"><h3><a href="/Services/hospitals/Services/Service/Team/DefaultView.aspx?id=104150">Staff</a></h3>
<div id="imageContent13b49c2304e540b680293193e384970a">
<div class="profile-pic">
<img alt="The MDT team" border="0" id="ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_PlaceHolderMain_column1Content_column1Content_TeamSummaryAndPhotoModule_PhotoView_DisplayImage" src="/Services/UserControls/UploadHandlers/MediaServerHandler.ashx?id=437"/>
</div>
</div>
<p>Being diagnosed with cancer can turn your life upside down - treatments required may disrupt your routine and plans, which is where the TYA service can help you. We aim to offer specialist age appropriate care, plus financial, emotional, psychological and social support and advice to young people who have a cancer diagnosis, as well as supporting your family, friends and those who are important to you.</p>
<p>There is a large dedicated team of professionals with a special interest in the care of young people. The team is made up of doctors, nurses, a youth support coordinator, learning mentor, social worker, psychologists, physiotherapists and pharmacists. As the cancer centre is a regional centre, we work closely with specialist teams in each type of cancer in order to ensure the best possible expert care is provided.</p><p><a href="/Services/hospitals/Services/Service/Team/DefaultView.aspx?id=104150">Learn more about our staff</a></p></div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
